IRS990.Desc: The organization provided general health and family planning services to its service area. During the year the Agency provided over 87,000 patient encounters under the Section 330 grant, Medicaid and Medicare.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: The organization provided dental services to its consumers in its service area at reduced rates based on their abiiity to pay.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE AGENCY ADOPTED THE PROVISIONS OF FASB ASC TOPIC 740-10, INCOME TAXES (PREVIOUSLY KNOW AS FASB INTERPRETATION NO. 48, ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES). MANAGEMENT BELIEVES IT HAS NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS, AND ACCORDINGLY THERE IS NO LIABILITY RECORDED FOR UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS AT YEAR-END.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CEO AND CFO OF THE AGENCY WILL PARTICIPATE IN COMPLETING THE FORM 990 AS WELL AS REVIEWING THE 990 BEFORE SUBMISSION. THE AGENCY'S CFO WILL REVIEW THE FORM 990 WITH THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 12c
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THIS POLICY IS PART OF A CODE OF CONDUCT THAT ALL EMPLOYEES AND THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS SIGN. IT IS ALSO PART OF THE BYLAWS OF THE AGENCY AND INCLUDED IN THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS ORIENTATION. THIS POLICY IS REVIEWED AT ANNUAL BOARD TRAININGS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION FOR KEY MANAGEMENT, INCLUDING THE CEO AND CFO, IS COMPARED TO REGIONAL & STATE SALARY SURVEYS BASED ON BUDGET, ANNUAL ENCOUNTERS, AND YEARS OF SERVICE. THIS SALARY SURVEY IS SPECIFIC TO COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS. SALARY COMPARISONS FOR KEY EMPLOYEES ARE ALSO COMPARED TO LOCAL SERVICE AREA PAY RATES IN ORDER TO REMAIN COMPETITIVE. THE CEO'S COMPENSATION PACKAGE IS DETERMINED, REVIEWED, AND APPROVED BY THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. ALL OTHER KEY EMPLOYEES' COMPENSATION IS DETERMINED BY THE CEO AND REVIEWED WITH THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: SALARY COMPARISONS FOR KEY EMPLOYEES ARE COMPARED TO LOCAL SERVICE AREA PAY RATES IN ORDER TO REMAIN COMPETITIVE. KEY EMPLOYEES' COMPENSATION IS DETERMINED BY THE CEO AND REVIEWED WITH THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE GENERAL PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
